│ int-sized distance, which can overflow/wrap for large 64-bit offsets and make widely separated stores appear    │
│ consecutive. The vectorizer then incorrectly folds them into a single vector store. A targeted fix is to make   │
│ the distance type wide enough and reject distances that don’t fit precisely. I will update RelatedStoreInsts to │
│ use 64-bit distances and add a guard to skip vectorization when getPointersDiff returns a distance that does    │
│ not round-trip in 32-bit (indicating potential truncation). This is a conservative change localized to          │
│ store-chain handling.                                                                                           │
