│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation stems from pointer distance wraparound when using 32-bit ints. A minimal and safe   │
│ fix is to widen the distance type used in store-chain grouping to 64-bit, without altering core algorithms. I   │
│ will update RelatedStoreInsts to use long long for distances (map key, insertOrLookup param, rebase param,      │
│ reverse_iterator pair), and adjust PrevDist in TryToVectorize to long long. This prevents wraparound-induced    │
│ false consecutivity while keeping behavior otherwise unchanged.                                                 │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ sed -i 's/using DistToInstMap = std::map<int, unsigned>/using DistToInstMap = std::map<long long, unsigned>/'   │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i 's/std::optional<unsigned> insertOrLookup(unsigned    │
│ InstrIdx, int PtrDist)/std::optional<unsigned> insertOrLookup(unsigned InstrIdx, long long PtrDist)/'           │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i 's/void rebase(unsigned MinSafeIdx, unsigned          │
│ NewBaseInstIdx, *int DistFromCurBase)/void rebase(unsigned MinSafeIdx, unsigned NewBaseInstIdx, long long       │
│ DistFromCurBase)/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i 's/std::pair<int,                  │
│ unsigned>/std::pair<long long, unsigned>/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i 's/int     │
│ PrevDist = -1;/long long PrevDist = -1;/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch       │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
