│ consecutive due to wraparound. A conservative, localized fix is to add a guard in the TryToVectorize lambda to  │
│ refuse vectorizing a store sequence if its pointer-distance span exceeds the maximum number of elements that    │
│ can fit in a vector register (MaxElts). This prevents forming a single wide vector store over non-contiguous    │
│ addresses while preserving normal small-span vectorizations.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                 │
